Name: Passenger Policy Add

Description: Adding passenger to a flight.

Preconditions: The passenger and flight are created.

Postconditions: The passenger will be added to a flight.

Basic Course of Action:

1. The use case begins when an admin wants to add passenger to a flight.

2. The system checks which type of flight is it. [Alt Course A, B]



Alternate Course A: BusinessFlight or PremiumFlight

A.3. The system checks if passenger is VIP [Alt Course D]

A.4. The system adds passenger and return True.

A.5. The use case ends.


Alternate Course D: Passenger is not a VIP

D.4. The system doesn't add passenger and return False.

D.5. The use case ends.


Alternate Course B: EconomyFlight

B.3. The system adds passenger and return True.

B.4. The use case ends.
